# Large binaries — never commit
*.gguf
*.dll
*.exe
dist/
build/
_build/
llama/
models/
git_log_output.txt
*.log
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.env
nova_drive_token.json

# ── SECRETS (2026-07-20, Cole) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# "Secrets are fine in folders and files. All files with secrets MUST be excluded from
# file repository uploads though (git and drive currently)."
#
# This list is mirrored in general_tools/nova_sync/drive.py (EXCLUDE_FILES +
# SECRET_SUFFIXES). The two MUST agree — a credential excluded from git but not from Drive
# has still left the machine. audit_scripts.py::check_secret_exclusions asserts parity, so
# adding to one without the other is now a HIGH finding rather than a silent leak.
nova_gateway.json
client_secrets.json
memory/.auth_token
memory/nova_users.json

# Secret-shaped names, anywhere in the tree
*.pem
*.key
*.p12
*.pfx
*.keystore
*_token.json
*_secret.json
*_secrets.json
*.credentials.json

# Regenerable artifacts / launcher junk
.nova_app_profile*/
build_exe/

# Cleanup archive (relocated clutter — safe to delete)
_admin/_archive_2026-05-23/

# Temp folders live beside the thing they belong to. Never tracked. (2026-07-14)
**/Temp/

# LanceDB store — regenerable data, 1000+ files (2026-07-14)
nova_memory_db/
prompt_cache/
